name: Took a walk down here this afternoon, figured I’d return
description:
Pacing wasn’t good at all but I wanted to quit at the 5k mark & didn’t so I count it as a win.
Was honestly surprised & happy that the legs could go for 10k. Very encouraging.
Definitely need/want to start eating healthier. This was fuelled by a big greasy breakfast this morning & a far from healthy dinner. Have felt sluggish/tired all day so yeah, overall I’m really happy with how this turned out. Gonna push that extra 60 metres next week to officially hit 10k hahaha.
